{You respond with your 5-card Major, 1\S.

Partner jumps to 3\H.  

With partner's 16-18 points you probably have enough strength for game.

With partner's six \Hs you have an 8-card fit.

So you bid 4\H.

North would play 4\H.

Click 

South plays 4\H. West leads \CA, \CK, \C4. East plays \C8 then \C2.

<b>South plays 4\H. West leads \CA, \CK, \C4. East plays \C8 then \C2.</b>

Losers: \S 0 : \H 0 : \D 1 : \C 3 : Total = 4

Suppose you discard a \D from dummy. If East doesn't ruff this \Cthen your \CQ will win. You could then try to establish dummy's \DQ to discard your fourth \C on. 

But you know that plan won't work because East <b>IS</b> going to ruff this \C if you discard. You only have one chance to make this contract, and that is the chance that East was not dealt the \HJ. So you ruff with dummy's \H10 and pray East doesn't over-ruff.

The prayer was answered, East did not hold the \HJ. 

So you won that trick and still had your \CQ to use after you pulled trumps.}
[Play "W"]CA

